SUMMARY:Building HIV Care in Rural America
DTSTART:20260516T000000Z
DTEND:20260516T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260607T072511Z
UID:97848259acbf6174@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Podcast - IDSA
DESCRIPTION:[Podcast: Let's Talk ID] Duration: 1858\n\nHost Mati Hlatshway
 o Davis\, MD\, MPH\, FIDSA\, is joined by Darrell McBride\, DO\, FIDSA\, f
 ormer program director and founder of the Geisinger Ryan White Program\, t
 o discuss the realities of delivering HIV and infectious diseases care in 
 rural communities. They explore barriers to care\, the role of telehealth 
 and public health partnerships\, and what it takes to build sustainable\, 
 equity-focused programs in underserved areas.\n\nEvent URL: https://www.bu
 zzsprout.com/2019912/episodes/19185942-building-hiv-care-in-rural-america.
 mp3\n\nSource: idsa_podcast
LOCATION:Podcast
URL:https://www.buzzsprout.com/2019912/episodes/19185942-building-hiv-care
 -in-rural-america.mp3
