BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:TWiV 1322: Clinical update with Dr. Daniel Griffin – Hantavirus 
 special
DTSTART:20260516T040000Z
DTEND:20260516T050000Z
DTSTAMP:20260607T072511Z
UID:018fd2b4cdda3b92@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Podcast - TWiV
DESCRIPTION:[Podcast: This Week in Virology]\n\nIn his weekly clinical upd
 ate\, Daniel Griffin and Vincent Racaniello reviewed the latest developmen
 ts surrounding the hantavirus outbreak\, including new interim guidance fr
 om the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention for the management of in
 fectious cases\, whether the CDC may be downplaying the significance of th
 e outbreak because of public backlash following the COVID-19 pandemic\, be
 fore Dr. Griffin deep dives into the measles outbreak\, recent statistics 
 RSV\, influenza and SARS-CoV-2 infections\, the Wasterwater Scan dashboard
 \, Johns Hopkins measles tracker\, benefit of maternal vaccination against
  RSV for infants\, efficacy and safety of a mRNA influenza vaccine &nbsp\;
 how to access and pay for Paxlovid\, where to go for answers about long CO
 VID-19\, multisystem inflammatory syndrome in children and contacting your
  federal government representative to stop the assault on science and biom
 edical research. Click arrow to play Download&nbsp\; TWiV 1322 (32 MB .mp3
 \, 53 min) Subscribe (free):&nbsp\; Apple Podcasts \, RSS \,&nbsp\; email 
 Become a&nbsp\; patron &nbsp\;of&nbsp\;TWiV! Links for this episode Interi
 m Guidance for Public Health Assessment and Management of People with Pote
 ntial Exposure to Andes Virus Outbreak (CDC) 3:36 Hantavirus in humans: a 
 review of clinical aspects and management (LANCET: Infectious Diseases) 15
 :21 “Super-Spreaders” and Person-to-Person Transmission of Andes Virus
  in Argentina (NEJM) 17:00 Person-to-Person Transmission of Andes Virus in
  Hantavirus Pulmonar\n\nEvent URL: https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1322/\
 n\nSource: twiv_podcast
LOCATION:Podcast
URL:https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1322/
