BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sleep Your Way to Health and Happiness
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260526T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260526T200000
DTSTAMP:20260607T072511Z
UID:36c9ca01836e73b7@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:Good sleep is critical to a healthy lifestyle. Studies have sh
 own that poor sleep is linked to higher body weight\, greater risk of hear
 t disease\, stroke\, type 2 diabetes\, inflammation\, and depression\, whi
 le good sleep can improve concentration and productivity\, athletic perfor
 mance\, and immune function. Yet for many of us\, a good night's sleep rem
 ains an elusive dream. One study by the CDC found that more than a third o
 f American adults are not getting enough sleep or good quality sleep on a 
 regular basis.\n\nJoin us in this noontime webinar to explore the science 
 of sleep. Learn how sleep is related to the core pillars of health -- exer
 cise\, diet\, and stress resilience. Gain information about what constitut
 es good sleep and how to spot common sleep disruptions. Finally\, learn ev
 idence-based techniques to improve sleep\, leading to better health\, resi
 liency\, and quality of life.\n\nThis class will be recorded and a one-wee
 k link to the recording will be shared with all registered participants. T
 o receive incentive points\, attend at least 80% of the live session or li
 sten to the entire recording within one week.  Request disability accommod
 ations and access info.\n\nClass details are subject to change.\n\nEvent U
 RL: https://events.stanford.edu/event/sleep-your-way-to-health-and-happine
 ss\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/sleep-your-way-to-health-and-happine
 ss
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Sleep Your Way to Health and Happiness
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
